I can't believe how long it took me to write a review for Mr. Currys. I guess it takes being away from the city to realize this is simply the BEST Indian restaurant I've ever been too.  Let's start with the food, the buffet selection is amazing - it offers an array of delicious chicken, lamb/goat, and vegetarian options. Some menus are rotating. All dishes are well prepared all FULL OF FLAVORS. Not to mention so many choices of chutneys/dips. I could never get tired of the dishes here. Btw, their ground lamb is usually pretty spicy but most other dishes do not have a lot of heat. They, however, have a rather mild but creamy taste that flatters the flavor of the ingredients themselves. I actually prefer that the dishes are not just masked by heavy spices.  Amazing Indian cuisine at a shockingly affordable price is not the only reason I came here. My favorite part has always been the owner of Mr. Curry's. He is the one of the nicest, kindest, and most genuine person I've ever met. He always warmed my heart whenever I came here. He would kindly offer tips and solutions for the most trivial questions I brought up. I hope he is doing well! I want to have the chance to say thank you to him again.  Their Chai is the most delicious but not aggressive I've ever had. They bottled the mix for sale for a while that literally made my day. I hope they bring it back. Btw they now offer takeouts priced by weight, so you can get fresh, hot, yummy food in small portions without worrying about wasting it. How great is that!  I'm a huge Asian food lover and this has been my favorite place to treat myself on a budget. Even the memory of it has made me disappointed by most other Indian restaurants I came across, be it in San Francisco or DC. I'd highly recommend it to anyone who enjoys a mild Indian cuisine or just need someone to talk to.

I found it unacceptable for them to have false promotions on their website. As I drove all the way from Belleville with the expectation of enjoying a lunch buffet at the special price of $8.75 which was not the case. As they have now increased their price to $9.95, but have yet to update their website. So although I walked in with an open mind I was already feeling a little let down. In all fairness to my experience with the food though. I did thoroughly enjoy the Aloo Sag and the Nan, but was highly dissappointed in all the other dishes being served. Which at the time of my visit were Lamb Vindaloo, Chicken Tikka Masala, Chicken Korma, Basmati Rice, Vegetable Biriyani, Channa Tikka Masala and Dal Sag. What I found myself most dissappointed with was the lack of authenticity in the flavor of the different dishes. Growing up one of my mothers best friends was of Indian decent and I was graciously afforded the opportunity of eating delicious authentic home cooked Indian cuisine quite often. So my level of expectation may be higher than others. I also found it quite ridiculous how small the cups were they made available for your beverage. As it was extremely inconvenient to continuously have to get up to refill your cup meanwhile your foods getting cold. The end all for me though was finding out about the $1.00 fee they wanted to charge me for paying with my card rather than paying with cash. Overall not the greatest experience, but if I happened to be in the area I'd stop in just to get some Aloo Sag & Nan to go.
